## ðŸ§© 3. Example: Nginx as Reverse Proxy for a C++ App

Letâ€™s say you wrote a REST API in C++ (Poco, Boost.Beast, or Crow):

```
[C++ app] runs on 127.0.0.1:8080
```

You can use Nginx to expose it publicly:

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name myapp.com;

    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8080;
    }
}
```

Now Nginx:

* Accepts requests on port 80
* Forwards them to your app
* Handles SSL, compression, logging, caching, etc.

Your app stays clean and lightweight. ðŸ’¡

